        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix refresh menu style",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Render only the persistent Refresh action with a custom AppKit row, aligned to native menu geometry.\n- Keep Settings, About, Quit, and other standard actions as native `NSMenuItem` rows so keyboard traversal and activation remain native.\n- Preserve the menu-open refresh interaction, busy-state gating, Command-R handling, hover styling, and final-width reconciliation.\n- Add focused regression coverage for row geometry, native action behavior, shortcut handling, refresh state, and provider-switcher resizing.\n\n## Runtime proof\n\n- Reproduced a 3-point Refresh alignment drift in 310-point Overview and Antigravity menus.\n- Verified identical final Refresh/Settings image and title origins (`x=17/37`) in both menus.\n- Verified hover geometry, persistent Refresh activation and return to idle, native Settings/About/Quit traversal and activation, and debug-only Command-Q behavior in the packaged app.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter 'StatusMenuPersistentRefreshTests|StatusMenuSwitcherRefreshTests|StatusMenuTests'`\n- `make test`\n- `make check`\n- Branch-wide Codex autoreview\n- Required GitHub CI\n",
